cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS

This paper discusses a method for pre-subtraction of known interference at the transmitter of a multiuser communication system, which falls under the category of information theory and communication. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of low-density parity check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in coding and information theory, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which suggests the use of computational methods, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
